<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="2349" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="22.[160,1156,851,1258]" box="[160,276,851,877]" pageId="22" pageNumber="2349">
<heading box="[160,276,851,877]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="22" pageNumber="2349" reason="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,851,877]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="2349" reason="3">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[160,1156,851,1258]" box="[160,891,886,912]" pageId="22" pageNumber="2349">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,224,886,912]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="2349" reason="3">Male.</emphasis>
Body length 5.0 
<emphasis box="[420,433,888,912]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="2349">â€“</emphasis>
<quantity box="[434,522,888,912]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="22" pageNumber="2349" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
. Antenna with 36 flagellomeres.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[160,1156,851,1258]" pageId="22" pageNumber="2349">
Head strongly convex, upper face with long projection and recurved; between antennal sockets with vertical ridge; dorsal margin of eyes with small triangular yellow spots. Malar space black (
<figureCitation box="[389,502,992,1016]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="19.[160,225,1328,1351]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1297]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[163,1153,142,1298]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 4. Head in frontal view. (a) Exochus argutus; (b) Exochus britannicus; (c) Exochus consimilis; (d) Exochus destitutus; (e) Exochus flavomarginatus; (f) Exochus frontellus; (g) Exochus gratus; (h) Exochus gravipes; (i) Exochus guttatus; (j) Exochus lictor; (k) Exochus lineifrons; (l) Exochus mitratus. Scale bar = 0.2 m m." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3993042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3993042/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="2349">Figure 4e</figureCitation>
). Pronotum weak sunken. Scutellum and postscutellum black, partly dark brown. Propodeum with area superomedia but sometimes indistinct (
<figureCitation box="[167,275,1061,1085]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="30.[160,225,1399,1422]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1369]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[163,1153,142,1369]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="Figure 7. Propodeum in dorsal view. (a) Exochus argutus; (b) Exochus britannicus; (c) Exochus consimilis; (d) Exochus destitutus; (e) Exochus flavomarginatus; (f) Exochus frontellus; (g) Exochus gratus; (h) Exochus gravipes; (i) Exochus guttatus; (j) Exochus lictor; (k) Exochus lineifrons; (l) Exochus mitratus. Scale bar = 0.2 m m." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3993048" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3993048/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="2349">Figure 7e</figureCitation>
); area externa with hair; area superomedia and area dentipara without hair; spiracle of propodeum oval, not connected pleural carina; metapleuron glabrous. Vein 
<emphasis box="[160,207,1130,1155]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="2349">cu-a</emphasis>
of hindwing intercepted at lower 0.3, with vein 
<emphasis box="[779,821,1130,1155]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="2349">Cu1</emphasis>
of hindwing trace. Tergite 1 with dorsal longitudinal carina, reach over at central area of tergite 1, upcurved in basal area; between dorsal longitudinal carinae without hair. Tergite 3 with epipleuron wedgeshaped, the basal part not convex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
